

\begin{itemize}

\item \textbf{Beat:} The smallest unit of rhythm. Counted as beats per minute. 
\item \textbf{Clap:} Set of beats. Denoted by the clap of the hand played periodically after a certain number of beats. If the time signature is 4/4, then 1 clap is played for every 4 beats, if time signature is 5/4, then 1 clap is played for every 5 beats.

\item \textbf{Pause:} Interval between the notes played in a rhythm pattern. Pauses refers to the places where notes are not played. Pause is measured in terms of number of beats of pause. 

\item \textbf{Duration:} Different way of calculating pauses. Refers the duration of each note played in the pattern. Duration is measured in terms of number of beats that note is played for. 

\item \textbf{Pattern:} Rhythm pattern that has a temporal sequence of notes and pauses played together, either as solo/accompaniment to a song. Some examples of patterns are:

\begin{enumerate}

\item "tha. tumki."
\item "tha thum thum tha"
\item "thum tha thum thum tha thum thum tha"

\end{enumerate}

\item \textbf{Phrase:} Refers to a melody phrase or the song.

\end{itemize}
